{"title":"The Cyclists’ Alliance’s 4 easy steps towards a better future for pro women cycling","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/03/12/the-cyclists-alliances-4-easy-steps-towards-a-better-future-for-pro-women-cycling/","date":1615577843000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p>This past Monday was International Women’s Day, and plenty of cycling industry brands joined in to celebrate &amp; promote women on bikes, both professionals &amp; recreational riders. But the last few weeks also reminded us of the huge winner payout gap between the top women &amp; men at the biggest UCI races. The <a href=\"https://cyclistsalliance.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Cyclists’ Alliance</a> wants to help make lasting change, and suggests four simple steps to help build a better future for women in pro cycling….</p><figure id=\"attachment_252924\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-252924\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135442/InternalionElles-Omloop-Het-Nieuwsblad-gender-pay-gap_ProCyclingStats-data.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135442/InternalionElles-Omloop-Het-Nieuwsblad-gender-pay-gap_ProCyclingStats-data.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x175/rscb8/ng:webp/ngcb8\" alt=\"InternationElles Omloop gender pay gap\" width=\"1000\" height=\"361\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135442/InternalionElles-Omloop-Het-Nieuwsblad-gender-pay-gap_ProCyclingStats-data.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x175/rscb8/ng:webp/ngcb8\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135442/InternalionElles-Omloop-Het-Nieuwsblad-gender-pay-gap_ProCyclingStats-data.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 1000w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135442/InternalionElles-Omloop-Het-Nieuwsblad-gender-pay-gap_ProCyclingStats-data-297x107.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135442/InternalionElles-Omloop-Het-Nieuwsblad-gender-pay-gap_ProCyclingStats-data-800x289.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135442/InternalionElles-Omloop-Het-Nieuwsblad-gender-pay-gap_ProCyclingStats-data-120x43.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135442/InternalionElles-Omloop-Het-Nieuwsblad-gender-pay-gap_ProCyclingStats-data-768x277.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135442/InternalionElles-Omloop-Het-Nieuwsblad-gender-pay-gap_ProCyclingStats-data-696x251.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 696w\" ezoid=\"0.6294793485926413\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135442/InternalionElles-Omloop-Het-Nieuwsblad-gender-pay-gap_ProCyclingStats-data.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 1000w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135442/InternalionElles-Omloop-Het-Nieuwsblad-gender-pay-gap_ProCyclingStats-data-297x107.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135442/InternalionElles-Omloop-Het-Nieuwsblad-gender-pay-gap_ProCyclingStats-data-800x289.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135442/InternalionElles-Omloop-Het-Nieuwsblad-gender-pay-gap_ProCyclingStats-data-120x43.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135442/InternalionElles-Omloop-Het-Nieuwsblad-gender-pay-gap_ProCyclingStats-data-768x277.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135442/InternalionElles-Omloop-Het-Nieuwsblad-gender-pay-gap_ProCyclingStats-data-696x251.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 696w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-252924\">c. <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/internationelles/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">InternationElles,</a> data by <a href=\"https://www.procyclingstats.com/index.php\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">ProCyclingStats</a></figcaption></figure><p>The conversation started with rider collective the <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/internationelles/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">InternationElles</a> questioning why World Champion Anna van der Breggan earned 1/17 of what Davide Ballerni did for winning the Spring Classics opener of Omloop Het Nieuwsblad – 930€ vs. 16,000€ – both of which delivered exciting racing. Fans of cycling and advocates for equality, quickly stood up with a goal to crowdfund a more-equal payout for the following week’s racing at Strade Bianche.</p><p><span><iframe width=\"696\" height=\"392\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\" data-ezsrc=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/aCOSoRAz6BE?version=3&amp;rel=1&amp;showsearch=0&amp;showinfo=1&amp;iv_load_policy=1&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en-US&amp;autohide=2&amp;wmode=transparent\"></iframe></span></p><p>And turnout they did, raising a total of 26,973€ in less than a week via a <a href=\"https://www.gofundme.com/f/equal-prize-money-for-the-womens-peloton\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">GoFundMe</a> set up by one Dutch fan. The fans made a statement ensuring that the top 5 finishing women racing the 2021 Strade Bianche outearned the men – combined with the organizer’s 6,298€ purse, the top women won 33,271€ vs. 31,600€ for the top-5 men. And former World Champ Chantal van den Broek-Blaak delivered an equally exciting sprint finish win in Sienna, as did Dutch champion Mathieu van der Poel.</p><figure id=\"attachment_252921\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-252921\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135047/The-Cyclist-Alliance_NL-Sporza-Cyclo-Cross-Worlds-viewership.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135047/The-Cyclist-Alliance_NL-Sporza-Cyclo-Cross-Worlds-viewership.jpg\" alt=\"The Cyclist Alliance NL Sporza CX World women' viewership\" width=\"1200\" height=\"675\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135047/The-Cyclist-Alliance_NL-Sporza-Cyclo-Cross-Worlds-viewership.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135047/The-Cyclist-Alliance_NL-Sporza-Cyclo-Cross-Worlds-viewership.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135047/The-Cyclist-Alliance_NL-Sporza-Cyclo-Cross-Worlds-viewership-297x167.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135047/The-Cyclist-Alliance_NL-Sporza-Cyclo-Cross-Worlds-viewership-800x450.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135047/The-Cyclist-Alliance_NL-Sporza-Cyclo-Cross-Worlds-viewership-120x68.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135047/The-Cyclist-Alliance_NL-Sporza-Cyclo-Cross-Worlds-viewership-768x432.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135047/The-Cyclist-Alliance_NL-Sporza-Cyclo-Cross-Worlds-viewership-696x392.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135047/The-Cyclist-Alliance_NL-Sporza-Cyclo-Cross-Worlds-viewership-1068x601.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135047/The-Cyclist-Alliance_NL-Sporza-Cyclo-Cross-Worlds-viewership-747x420.jpg 747w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135047/The-Cyclist-Alliance_NL-Sporza-Cyclo-Cross-Worlds-viewership.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135047/The-Cyclist-Alliance_NL-Sporza-Cyclo-Cross-Worlds-viewership-297x167.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135047/The-Cyclist-Alliance_NL-Sporza-Cyclo-Cross-Worlds-viewership-800x450.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135047/The-Cyclist-Alliance_NL-Sporza-Cyclo-Cross-Worlds-viewership-120x68.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135047/The-Cyclist-Alliance_NL-Sporza-Cyclo-Cross-Worlds-viewership-768x432.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135047/The-Cyclist-Alliance_NL-Sporza-Cyclo-Cross-Worlds-viewership-696x392.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135047/The-Cyclist-Alliance_NL-Sporza-Cyclo-Cross-Worlds-viewership-1068x601.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135047/The-Cyclist-Alliance_NL-Sporza-Cyclo-Cross-Worlds-viewership-747x420.jpg 747w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-252921\">c. <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/thecyclistsalliance/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">The Cyclists’ Alliance</a></figcaption></figure><p>But that was meant to send a message to race organizers, as crowdfunded general parity is obviously not a sustainable funding strategy. But even after women’s racing drew in more Sporza viewership than the men at cyclocross World’s last month, it seems like a good time to revisit how to best support professional women’s cycling.</p><figure id=\"attachment_252920\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-252920\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135031/The-Cyclist-Alliance_4-easy-steps-to-a-better-future-for-pro-women-cycling.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135031/The-Cyclist-Alliance_4-easy-steps-to-a-better-future-for-pro-women-cycling.jpg\" alt=\"The Cyclist Alliance 4 steps for better pro women cycling future\" width=\"2000\" height=\"555\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135031/The-Cyclist-Alliance_4-easy-steps-to-a-better-future-for-pro-women-cycling.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135031/The-Cyclist-Alliance_4-easy-steps-to-a-better-future-for-pro-women-cycling.jpg 2000w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135031/The-Cyclist-Alliance_4-easy-steps-to-a-better-future-for-pro-women-cycling-297x82.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135031/The-Cyclist-Alliance_4-easy-steps-to-a-better-future-for-pro-women-cycling-800x222.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135031/The-Cyclist-Alliance_4-easy-steps-to-a-better-future-for-pro-women-cycling-120x33.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135031/The-Cyclist-Alliance_4-easy-steps-to-a-better-future-for-pro-women-cycling-768x213.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135031/The-Cyclist-Alliance_4-easy-steps-to-a-better-future-for-pro-women-cycling-1536x426.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135031/The-Cyclist-Alliance_4-easy-steps-to-a-better-future-for-pro-women-cycling-696x193.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135031/The-Cyclist-Alliance_4-easy-steps-to-a-better-future-for-pro-women-cycling-1068x296.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135031/The-Cyclist-Alliance_4-easy-steps-to-a-better-future-for-pro-women-cycling-1920x533.jpg 1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135031/The-Cyclist-Alliance_4-easy-steps-to-a-better-future-for-pro-women-cycling-1514x420.jpg 1514w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135031/The-Cyclist-Alliance_4-easy-steps-to-a-better-future-for-pro-women-cycling.jpg 2000w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135031/The-Cyclist-Alliance_4-easy-steps-to-a-better-future-for-pro-women-cycling-297x82.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135031/The-Cyclist-Alliance_4-easy-steps-to-a-better-future-for-pro-women-cycling-800x222.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135031/The-Cyclist-Alliance_4-easy-steps-to-a-better-future-for-pro-women-cycling-120x33.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135031/The-Cyclist-Alliance_4-easy-steps-to-a-better-future-for-pro-women-cycling-768x213.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135031/The-Cyclist-Alliance_4-easy-steps-to-a-better-future-for-pro-women-cycling-1536x426.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135031/The-Cyclist-Alliance_4-easy-steps-to-a-better-future-for-pro-women-cycling-696x193.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135031/The-Cyclist-Alliance_4-easy-steps-to-a-better-future-for-pro-women-cycling-1068x296.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135031/The-Cyclist-Alliance_4-easy-steps-to-a-better-future-for-pro-women-cycling-1920x533.jpg 1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135031/The-Cyclist-Alliance_4-easy-steps-to-a-better-future-for-pro-women-cycling-1514x420.jpg 1514w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-252920\">c. <a href=\"https://cyclistsalliance.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">The Cyclists’ Alliance</a></figcaption></figure><p>The Cyclists’ Alliance’s Rider Council suggests four simple steps: Watch the women’s races, engage with women’s racing, follow the teams &amp; riders, and call out inequality when you see it. Some of those are easier to do than say, but The Cyclists’ Alliance offers great tips on how easy it can be to do each one.</p><figure id=\"attachment_252919\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-252919\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135021/Womens-pro-bike-check.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135021/Womens-pro-bike-check.jpg\" alt=\"Bikerumor Pro Bike Check 4 steps for better pro women cycling future\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135021/Womens-pro-bike-check.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135021/Womens-pro-bike-check.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135021/Womens-pro-bike-check-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135021/Womens-pro-bike-check-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135021/Womens-pro-bike-check-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135021/Womens-pro-bike-check-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135021/Womens-pro-bike-check-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135021/Womens-pro-bike-check-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135021/Womens-pro-bike-check-630x420.jpg 630w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135021/Womens-pro-bike-check.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135021/Womens-pro-bike-check-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135021/Womens-pro-bike-check-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135021/Womens-pro-bike-check-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135021/Womens-pro-bike-check-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135021/Womens-pro-bike-check-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135021/Womens-pro-bike-check-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/12135021/Womens-pro-bike-check-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-252919\">recent Bikerumor women’s Pro Bike Checks</figcaption></figure><p>What we can do best at Bikerumor is spreading the word. We don’t cover racing, but we are always happy to cover the tech of the pro women. It looks like over the last four years or so, we’ve shared about 2x as many men’s <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/?s=pro+bike+check\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Pro Bike Checks</a> as we have for the women. So that’s something we can try to improve on. #StriveForFairness</p><p>Find out more how to make a difference at: <a href=\"https://cyclistsalliance.org/2021/03/four-simple-steps-to-help-build-a-better-future-for-professional-womens-cycling-from-our-rider-council/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">CyclistsAlliance.org</a></p></div></div>","author":"Cory Benson","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"7bce6bf36cd040e9c7e4e3c4e4ff94578f83d292de0fe1a403873fbf49fe5820","category":"Cycling"}